Items.Title: Old Melbourne Jail Crime and Justice Experience
Items.Subtitle: Melbourne's Oldest Prison
Items.Description: Melbourne's oldest prison, where some of Australia's most infamous were inprisoned, including Ned Kelly and Squizzy Taylor.
Items.Content:
Visit the original Gaol and explore all 3 levels including the execution area and see Ned Kelly's Death mask. Join the Charge Sergeant on a tour of the cells when you visit the Watch house. Take a night tour with the Hangman or join our Ghost..What Ghost? evening tour. Take part in the recreation of a famous trial in Court One of the Old Magistrate's Court during school holidays. Find out more about the Gaol's fascinating history, how to book the Gaol for a function or bring your school group for an educational program.You can see the execution area and tour the cells or take part in the recreation of a famous trail.

Location:
337 Russell Street
Melbourne VIC 3000

To Contact Them
Phone: 8663 7228
info@oldmelbournegaol.com.au
www.oldmelbournegaol.com.au

Opening Hours
Monday through to Sunday including Public Holidays: 9.30am-5pm
* Closed Good Friday and Christmas Day.

The gaol is wheelchair accessible

All payment types accepted.

Items.Title: Australian Centre for Contemporary Art (ACCA)
Items.Subtitle: Art Museum
Items.Description: The Australian Centre For Contemporary Art is a contemporary art gallery in Melbourne, Australia.
Items.Content:
ACCA is Melbourne's leading contemporary art museum and presents the latest and most significent artworks from around the world 

Location:
111 Sturt Street
Southbank VIC 3006

To Contact Them
Phone: 8663 7228
info@accaonline.org.au
www.accaonline.org.au

Opening Hours
Tuesday through to friday including Public Holidays: 10.00am-5pm
Saturday and Sunday: 11.00am-6pm
Not open Mondays except by appointment
* Closed Good Friday and Christmas Day.

The museum is wheelchair accessible.
